Clark Kent that's not going to happen. 

But as a woman, it likely wouldn't bother me nearly as much as it would bother you.

My ideal future of equality is this: we look at each individual as an individual, and let them be who they are. People should pursue their talents, regardless of gender. If a woman is good at making a living, she should do that. If a man is good at nurturing children, he should do that. If an action is good, it's good, whether pretend by either gender. If it's bad, it's bad, and consequences shouldn't be based on gender. If we to to stop stuffing people into boxes, they'll accomplish more.

As far as whether this awards show was unequal, I don't know or really care at this point. I don't watch awards shows. But if there's an awards show with all female announcers and everyone involved is fine with it, great. I'm sure there have been many with all make announcers in the past. I hope not in the future though. In the future, it'd be nice if all the announcers were just people.

Yes, things are fraught between the genders right now, and we might see a little more "inequality" in favor of women. It's like a pendulum swinging. It was caught on the men's side for a long time, and now it's swinging a bit to the women's side. With any luck it'll settle in the middle soon enough.
